  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we managed to get through those fence, and we came close to the border, to the Russian-Polish border.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] By the way, I always remember that the place, it was Malkin, but it-- in my, in my mind, it was a story, you know.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I knew there was a place Malkin, and we passed it, and there was the border, and-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] but two years ago when I was in Poland and on the way to Treblinka, they stopped the bus, and they said, here is Malkin, Malkinia in Polish.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I said, oh, that's where it was, now.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now this place became more real in my mind.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "OK, so we, we came to the, to the Russian border, and we were sitting there with thousands and thousands of people.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we couldn't get through the other side.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Finally, somebody told my mother-- [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] it was a kind of an isolated place and there weren't much houses around it, but in the distance we could see some isolated places, houses where people were, were living.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And while we were sitting there for about two weeks, as I said, somebody told my mother, you know, why don't you try to get the soldiers to let you through?",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You just ask him that you are here with two little children, and [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] you didn't wash them, and they didn't have anything warm for, for them.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe they let you get into the house.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Tell them after that you'll come back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if you succeed, once you are there, you'll see, maybe you can continue to go.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So my mother tried it, and-- first, first of all, you couldn't get close to any soldier, you know.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
